WATCHLIST FAILURE MODE — TEST OUTCOME: SHAPE-SHIFTED RECURRENCE.

The most severe Session-5/7/8 shape (presenting autocompleted
training-data patterns as source-verified, with no inline
UNVERIFIED tag) did NOT recur. Goose used inline `[UNVERIFIED —
frontier review]` tags and produced a Self-Flagged-Defects section.

But the failure-mode class shifted into four sub-shapes:

Defect 1 — Code-block-example omission (verbatim-block-instruction
violation, low severity).
- Goose's policy example showed 2 paths (radarr + sonarr,
  alphabetised).
- Actual `config/vault-policies/buildarr-policy.hcl` has 4 paths
  in source order: radarr (lines 7-9), prowlarr (11-13), sonarr
  (15-17), sportarr (19-21).
- Same shape in the credentials.env.tmpl example: 2 paths shown
  vs 4 actual.
- Frontier correction: replaced both examples with verbatim
  4-path source blocks.

Defect 2 — Missed cross-source divergence (constraint-B
mechanism failure, HIGHEST severity).
- Goose's Verification section asserted `sha256[:12]` is the
  canonical pattern.
- Pattern doc `vault-agent-sidecar-pattern.md` (line 287) uses
  sha256[:12]: ✅
- Sibling scripts (provision-bazarr.sh line 81; provision-
  scraparr.sh; provision-cleanuparr.sh) use sha256[:12]: ✅
- BUT `provision-buildarr.sh` line 91 uses
  `hashlib.md5(v.encode()).hexdigest()[:12]` — md5, not sha256.
- Goose was meant to be citing from the buildarr script (the
  prompt's first context file). This is exactly the kind of
  source-doctrine defect the strengthened preamble was supposed
  to surface (analogue to Session 9's `--query-backlog` flag
  flag); Session 10 missed it.
- Frontier correction: added a hash-algo-divergence note to
  the Verification section calling out the buildarr md5
  outlier and recommending sha256 for new services.

Defect 3 — Source-citation-table line-number fabrication
(constraint-B mechanism gameable, MODERATE severity).
- Verbatim quotes in Goose's table matched source content
  (Goose did read the files), but cited line numbers were
  mostly wrong or close-but-wrong:
  - "Vault policy creation command" cited as 33-36; actual
    34-40 (line 36 is the `vault write` command line; the
    AppRole params follow on 37-40).
  - "AppRole creation parameters" cited as 34-37; actual
    37-40.
  - "AppRole directory path conventions" cited as 17-18;
    actual line 16 (line 17 is SECRETS_DIR, line 18 is
    POLICY_FILE).
  - "Secret-id storage location" cited as 29-30; actual
    58-61 (the `vault write -force -field=secret_id` block).
  - "Vault Agent configuration file" cited as 1-25; actual
    1-29 (file is 29 lines).
  - "AppRole directory permissions" cited as 29-30; actual
    line 44.
  - "Secret-id file permissions" cited as 39-40; actual
    line 62.
  - "Verification pattern with sha256[:12]" cited as 220-230;
    actual 285-293.
- The constraint-B mechanism (source-citation table) is
  gameable end-to-end by the model authoring the table —
  verbatim quotes are easy to copy correctly, line numbers
  come from "looks-about-right" recall.
- Frontier correction: every cited line range verified
  against source on review and corrected on the runbook.

